BENONI - Gauteng police have discovered eight more bodies suspected to be illegal miners in Benoni.This brings the total number of bodies found since Sunday to 14.READ: Zama zamas want to rescue trapped minersSix people were initially found on Sunday morning and the remaining individuals were discovered on Monday afternoon at Unity Street. The motive for the killing might be linked to the rival gangs involved in an illegal mining. It appears that the victims were either killed with a sharp object or shot before their bodies were dumped, said a statement issued by the police on Monday.READ: Illegal mining: A look into their worldThe victims have not yet been identified. Police are appealing to anyone with information to contact the nearest police station.eNCA